.006), stroke (HR = 3.06[1.44-6.51], p = 0.004), and mortality (HR = 1.73[1.08-2.78], p = 0.02). After adjustment for vascular risk factors, all the associations described Abetaove were unchanged, except the association of CBI with mortality which was no longer significant. Neither WMH nor CBI were associated with MCI-A. Conclusions: In a large community sample of middle-aged adults the presence of either WMH or CBI increased the risk of subsequent MCI-EF and dementia, CBI increased risk of incident stroke and extensive WMH was associated with increased mortality, emphasizing the value of these MRI measures as markers of cumulated vascular injury and predictors of adverse outcome independently of vascular risk factors.},
